The emergency medical systems (EMS) in Europe are of a high quality partly due 
to the presence of an emergency doctor at the scene. In those countries without 
emergency doctors in the field, the emergency medical technicians (EMT) are 
allowed by law to carry out medical interventions due to their special education 
including more than 2000 hrs of first aid training (paramedics). The efficiency 
of the EMS is essentially improved by the presence of paramedics, especially in 
