life expectancy is low (< or = 70 a) bystander training is rarely introduced. 
The EMS in Austria is of European standard in the structure of the rescue chain. 
Some links of this chain require correction and improvement: bystander training 
has not yet reached its optimal expanse; the profession of an EMT has to be 
urgently recognized by law; the gaping difference between EMS in urban areas and 
rural areas has to be eliminated; the limited capacity of emergency admittance 
to hospitals is a weak link in the chain of survival.

