Elevated dihydrofolate reductase and impaired methotrexate transport as elements 
in methotrexate resistance in childhood acute lymphoblastic leukemia.

Matherly LH(1), Taub JW, Ravindranath Y, Proefke SA, Wong SC, Gimotty P, Buck S, 
Wright JE, Rosowsky A.

Author information:
(1)Developmental Therapeutics Program, Michigan Cancer Foundation, Detroit 
48201.

A retrospective study of clinical resistance to methotrexate (MTX) was performed 
on 29 archival specimens of frozen lymphoblasts obtained from children with 
acute lymphoblastic leukemia (ALL), including 19 at initial presentation and 10 
